    Product Description

    Providing peace of mind, Defender Guard Pro plug in power outdoor security camera allows you to monitor activity outside of your home or business from anywhere. Featuring crystal clear optics and audio, expandable storage and simple, yet secure sharing options, our smart security camera system provides the details you need to protect your loved ones, your property and your privacy. Equipped with a 2K high-definition video camera with digital zoom, our Guard Pro surveillance camera allows you to clearly see every detail. The camera includes full-color night vision for greater clarity in low-light areas and crisp two-way audio to listen and speak to visitors, delivery drivers and intruders. Minimizing false alarms, our home security camera is armed with smart human detection. This reduces alerts due to insects, small animals and swaying branches. Set the outside camera to continuously record, create a schedule or use the motion-activated mode. Our 2.4 GHz WiFi camera utilizes our proprietary SecureGuard bank-level encryption to ensure every moment remains private until you are ready to share. Free storage on the included 32GB micro SD card, the spotlight camera records even when the Wi-Fi is down. Empowering homeowners, renters and businesses for over 20 years, our team at Defender is dedicated to providing cutting-edge solutions for security. Clearvu and Secureguard are both trademarks of Empowerment Technologies Inc.

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    Amazon Customer
    4 out of 5 stars
    Very easy to setup and catches most events and labels them by human vs vehicle
    I just installed this wireless security camera and I like the quality and notifications. These cameras accept a microSD card as well. Works better than my older Ring camera where you just see the person leaving your front door or see the tail end of the car. This camera is always on and captures a few seconds before the trigger event occurs so you can see what triggered the security notification. Very easy to setup on your network (supports both wired and wireless). I have an battery powered camera setup to monitor the same area but this Defender security camera does not miss trigger events like the competitor. I like how the camera lights come on when it triggers and switches from IR black and white video to a color video, this can be turned off.Its great to receive notifications based on humans vs vehicles. Although, onetime it misidentified a deer, that was crossing the street, as a human.LOLBuild quality is solid with painted metallic body and protective covering for the power cable if exposed to the elements. The wifi network connectivity is a big plus for locations that are not accessible via wired ethernet cable. The quality of this device, accuracy of results has me looking at replacing my longtime quirky Lorex security system with a newer NVR system.One drawback I see is the lack of Power-over-Ethernet (POE) when connected to ethernet in wired mode. You have to plug in the power cable as well as the ethernet cable unless you are using in wireless mode. I also notice that when video playback occurs it is very jumpy initially. You have to play it a second or third time to get a smoother playback so the Defender Guard app needs tweaking to improve efficiency.You get a 128GB microSD and a 2 year extended warranty for this price. You can purchase a separate SKU without the warranty for less so you can shop for your budget.

    • Lon
      5.0 out of 5 stars Easy setup, works over WiFi, Guard Pro app good, image quality excellent, no app for Windows.
      Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2025
      Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
      I ordered this WiFi security camera to use on a house I rented. It replaces one left by a previous tenant so there was already a hole to run the power cord. I needed a WiFi camera because the landlord wont allow any additional holes to run a hard-wired camera cable through the house. This camera requires 1 hole for the power cord, but everything else (video, voice, control) runs over WiFi.

      I mounted this camera above the garage door pointed at the driveway and street. The 110-degree angle of view covers the whole driveway and a little extra on both sides, but I wish I had a wider view. To cover the whole frontage of the house really calls for using two cameras, but since I am limited by the landlord to use only the existing hole, I am stuck with just one.

      The installation and setup was straightforward using the Guard Pro app on my Samsung S22 Ultra phone. I just followed the instructions and it connected to my phone and WiFi network without any problems. The Guard Pro app is reasonably intuitive and I found it easier to use after having used it for a few days and became used to the menu selections.

      The image quality of 4K (8MP) provides very good detail that allows you to zoom and get more detail. You can read a license plate of a parked car, but dont expect to capture plates of cars that drive by. Overall picture quality is very good and the best images are captured in daylight.

      One drawback, in my opinion, is the lack of a Windows compatible app to view and control the camera. I find it useful to view images on a larger screen than my phone, but the Guard Pro app does not work on the Windows platform. There are emulators that allow you to run an Android app on your computer, but they still confine the image size to that of a cell phone, so there is not much point in that. I should mention that it is possible to share a video clip and send it by email to your Windows computer, then view the clip using an MP4 viewer which fills the whole screen, so that is one possible workaround for viewing on a Windows device.

      I have chosen not to purchase the cloud storage which is offered. The camera detects motion, vehicles, and people, then stores the images on a MicroSD card in the camera. The MicroSD card can be accessed with a Phillips screwdriver, but I can use my phone to download clips, view live images, and control the camera, so I havent found the need to access the MicroSD card yet.

      Overall, this camera was easy to install and is easy to use with a phone. It does a good job of providing good quality images in high resolution without any monthly costs.

    • Jason Lee
      5.0 out of 5 stars No fees, excellent video quality
      Reviewed in the United States on February 17, 2025
      Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
      The Defender Guard Pro Camera is an excellent value for your dollar, and the first reason I was interested in this camera is because there are no monthly fees required to use the camera. There is an option for paid cloud storage, but you can use an SD card in the camera for local storage at no cost.

      The camera itself feels robust and records in high quality, the images are clear and free of distortion, and the camera also has a night mode that offers higher contrast images since it has lights on the camera. The camera is easy to set up and can be connected either via an ethernet cable or via WiFi. Since this is a powered camera, just be sure you have a way to get the power cable from your camera to a plug. The camera is easy to mount since there is a sticker template matching the back plate, and mounting screws are included.

      The phone application is also easy to use. You can see your footage in real time, and recordings stored on your camera. The camera is capable of detecting humans, cars, pets and you can also configure its zones for sending alerts so it's not going off every time a car goes by. Not much to the set up of the app either, just creating a basic account and moving on, and it is nice that it does not require too much information.

      Overall, this is a low cost and high value camera that makes it easy for anyone to add eyes to the front or back of their house. There are a lot of solutions out there, but with no recurring fees, high quality recordings, and a friendly app, this camera is a great option if you are considering a security camera.
